==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lyrical
<hw>Lyr"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>lyricus</ets>, Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>lyrique</ets>. See <er>Lyre</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to a lyre or harp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fitted to be sung to the lyre;</def> <specif>hence,
also,</specif> <def>appropriate for song; suitable for or suggestive of
singing; -- of music or poetry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>expressing deep personal emotion; -- said especially
of poetry which expresses the individual emotions of the poet; <as>as,
the dancer's <ex>lyrical</ex> performance</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Sweet
<xex>lyric</xex> song.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lyric.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lyric</ent>⟦br⟧
